{
  "texts": [
    "A recent review showed that artificial neural networks are quickly gaining traction as a digital technology to convert text into such maps (Ködding et al., 2023).",
    "In particular, deep neural networks such as Large-Scale Pre-Trained Language Models (PLMs) can be given a source text and guided through a conversation to gradually tease out a map, as simplified in Fig. 2.",
    "Such prototypes have been built on BERT and produced either a mind map (Feblowitz et al., 2021) or a form of causal map (Davis et al., 2022).",
    "This specific use of a PLM is known as a question-answering (Q&A) system.",
    "Starting with the text and an initial topic or question, the Q&A system retrieves the answer from the text."
  ]
}